'''''Murphy High School''''' (MHS) in [[Murphy, North Carolina|Murphy]], [[North Carolina]] serves grades 9-12 and is one of only three high schools in the [[Cherokee_County_(North_Carolina)_School_District|Cherokee County School District]]. As of 2007 it had an active enrollment of 519 students and a full time teaching staff of 42 teachers giving an average of 12 students per teacher.<ref>[http://cherokeecounty.nc.schoolwebpages.com/education/school/school.php?sectiondetailid=550& Murphy High School - School Home<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.psk12.com/rating/USindivphp/SchID_300386.html Murphy,Elementary School,Cherokee County, North Carolina<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It was given a greatschools rating of 6/10 and an average community rating of 4/5 stars. <ref>[http://www.greatschools.org/north-carolina/murphy/496-Murphy-High-School/ Murphy High School - Murphy, North Carolina - NC - School overview<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
